author: Jonas T. Ulbrich

This specification is written in RQMT.

The language has been intentionally employed to define its own
structure, semantics, and behavioral requirements.

This recursive definition serves both as the normative specification
of the language and as a demonstration of its ability to represent
structured requirements in a human-readable and machine-processable
form.


req-1 RQMT Language Specification:
    An implementation shall be considered compliant if it satisfies all
    mandatory requirements defined herein.

    req-2 Scope:
        The specification shall define:
        - The lexical structure of the language.
        - The syntactic structure of the language.
        - The semantic interpretation of language constructs.
        - The requirements imposed on compliant implementations.

    req-3 Language Principles:
        The language shall:
        - Remain human-readable.
        - Remain machine-processable.
        - Support deterministic parsing.
        - Support traceability.
        - Support tooling integration.
        - Preserve compatibility with version control workflows.

    req-4 Abstract Syntax Tree:
        An RQMT document shall be representable as an Abstract Syntax Tree.

        req-5 Document Node:
            The root node of the AST shall represent the active document.

        req-6 Requirement Node:
            Requirement declarations shall produce requirement nodes.

        req-7 Attribute Node:
            Attribute declarations shall produce attribute nodes.

        req-8 Text Node:
            Rich text content shall produce text nodes.

    req-76 Document Text Node:
        Rich text content located at the document root shall produce
        document text nodes.

        req-77 Document Text Format:
            Document text shall support Markdown syntax.

    req-9 Lexical Structure:
        req{req_keywords}-10 Requirement Keywords:
            The following keywords shall define requirement nodes:
            - req
            - fr
            - nfr
            - br
            - ur
            - sr

            req-11 Keyword Recognition:
                Requirement keywords shall only be recognized at the beginning
                of a logical line following optional indentation.

            req-12 Keyword Isolation:
                Keywords appearing within arbitrary text shall not be interpreted
                as requirement declarations.

        req{attr_keywords}-13 Attribute Keywords:
            Attributes shall be identified through reserved attribute names.

            req-14 Document Attributes:
                The following document attributes shall be supported:
                - author
                - date

            req-15 Requirement Attributes:
                The following requirement attributes shall be supported:
                - id
                - author
                - date
                - title
                - description

    req-16 Requirement Identity:
        req-17 Requirement Identifier:
            Every requirement shall possess exactly one identifier.

        req-18 Identifier Syntax:
            Requirement identifiers shall be positive integer values.

        req-19 Identifier Uniqueness:
            Requirement identifiers shall be unique within a document.

        req-20 Identifier Stability:
            Requirement identifiers should remain stable throughout the
            lifetime of a requirement.

        req-21 Alias:
            Requirements may define an alias.

        req-22 Alias Purpose:
            Aliases shall provide human-readable references to requirements.

        req-23 Alias Uniqueness:
            Aliases shall be unique within a document.

        req-24 Alias Optionality:
            Aliases shall be optional.

    req-25 Syntax:
        req-26 Requirement Declaration:
            A requirement shall be defined by a requirement keyword.

        req-27 Requirement Identifier Syntax:
            A requirement identifier shall be declared through the sequence:
            `<requirement keyword>-<identifier>`, see {req_keywords}

        req-28 Requirement Alias Syntax:
            A requirement alias shall be declared through the sequence:
            `<requirement keyword>{<alias>}`, see {req_keywords}

        req-29 Combined Alias And Identifier Syntax:
            A requirement alias and identifier shall be declared through the sequence:
            `<requirement keyword>{<alias>}-<identifier>`, see {req_keywords}

        req-30 Title Definition:
            A title shall be implicitly defined by text immediately following
            the requirement declaration and preceding the first unescaped
            colon on the logical line.

            req-31 Title Line Constraint:
                Titles shall not span multiple lines.

        req-32 Description Definition:
            Requirement descriptions shall be defined by rich text content
            associated with a requirement.

            req-78 Brief Description:
                A brief description may be defined on the same logical line
                as the requirement declaration.

            req-79 Brief Description Interpretation:
                Text following the first unescaped colon on a requirement
                declaration line shall be interpreted as the brief
                description.

            req-80 Brief Description Format:
                Brief descriptions shall be interpreted as plain text.

            req-33 Description Format:
                Requirement descriptions shall support Markdown syntax.

        req-34 Attribute Definition:
            Attributes shall be defined through the sequence:
            `<attribute keyword>: <value>`, see {attr_keywords}

            req-35 Multiline Values:
                Attribute values may span multiple lines.

    req-81 Escaping:
        Reserved syntax characters may be escaped through a preceding
        backslash.

        req-82 Escaped Colon:
            An escaped colon shall not terminate a title.
            
    req-36 Hierarchy:
        req-37 Indentation:
            Indentation shall define parent-child relationships.

        req-38 Parent Resolution:
            A node shall become a child of the nearest valid node with
            a lower indentation level.

        req-39 Hierarchical Requirements:
            Requirements may contain child requirements.

        req-40 Hierarchical Attributes:
            Attributes shall belong to the nearest valid parent node.

    req-41 References:
        req-42 Alias References:
            Requirements may be referenced through aliases.

        req-43 Local References:
            References to requirements within the current document shall
            be expressed through:
            `{alias}`

        req-44 Relative References:
            References to requirements in external documents shall be
            expressed through:
            `{reference}`

        req-45 Reference Structure:
            References shall be composed of components separated by dots.

        req-46 Relative Path Prefix:
            Leading dots shall denote relative filesystem traversal.

            req-47 Current Directory:
                A single leading dot shall denote the current directory.

            req-48 Parent Directory:
                Additional leading dots shall denote traversal to parent
                directories.

        req-49 Reference Component Resolution:
            The final component of a reference shall identify the
            referenced requirement.

            req-50 Directory Components:
                Components preceding the target requirement shall
                identify directories and files.

        req-51 Reference Resolution:
            References shall be resolved during semantic analysis.

        req-52 Requirement Target:
            References shall resolve to requirements only.

        req-53 Invalid Reference Target:
            References which do not resolve to a requirement shall be
            invalid.

        req-54 Invalid References:
            Unresolved references shall generate diagnostics.

    req-55 Diagnostics:
        req-56 Lexical Diagnostics:
            Invalid lexical constructs shall generate diagnostics.

        req-57 Syntax Diagnostics:
            Invalid syntactic constructs shall generate diagnostics.

        req-58 Semantic Diagnostics:
            Invalid semantic constructs shall generate diagnostics.

        req-59 Duplicate Identifier Diagnostics:
            Duplicate identifiers shall generate diagnostics.

        req-60 Duplicate Alias Diagnostics:
            Duplicate aliases shall generate diagnostics.

        req-61 Invalid Reference Diagnostics:
            Invalid references shall generate diagnostics.

    req-62 Tooling:
        req-63 Reference Navigation:
            Tooling implementations should provide navigation support
            for references.

        req-64 Hover Information:
            Tooling implementations should provide hover information
            for valid references.

        req-65 Hover Path Resolution:
            Hover information should display the resolved location of
            referenced requirements.

        req-66 Go To Definition:
            Tooling implementations should provide navigation from
            references to requirement declarations.

        req-67 Find References:
            Tooling implementations should provide navigation from
            requirement declarations to their references.

        req-68 Auto Completion:
            Tooling implementations should provide auto completion
            for references.

        req-69 Reference Path Completion:
            Auto completion should suggest valid path components.

        req-70 Reference Requirement Completion:
            Auto completion should suggest valid requirement targets.

    req-71 Future Extensions:

        req-72 Cross Repository References:
            Future revisions may support references between repositories.

        req-73 Traceability Metadata:
            Future revisions may support explicit traceability constructs.

        req-74 Test Integration:
            Future revisions may support test artifact integration.

        req-75 Validation Constraints:
            Future revisions may support user-defined validation rules.
